aline, and logic both brutal and brilliant. Join Parker on his jobs and read them all again or for the first time. But don’t talk to the law.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  acrime fiction, noir, roman noirs, hard-bitten mysteries, mystery, thriller, suspense, action, thrilling adventure, prison escape, violence, gunplay, con artists, heists, convicts, bad boys, flawed hero, cops, police investigations, locked up, jail time, snitches, master thief, harsh, brutal, fast-paced, hard-boiled, parker novels, breakout, career criminal, dark humor, gritty, big city, crooks, killers, plot twists, danger, ultimate score.1 aHolm, Chris.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311071193640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226508344423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226508344/original  a978-3-11-071193-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles